node.statement: F-symbols (eq 2.6): The 2x2 F-matrix is [[1/xi, 1/sqrt(xi)], [1/sqrt(xi), -1/xi]]. Proof: (a) From bubble moves and fusion rules, contracting external legs gives constraints. (b) Pentagon identity uniquely determines F up to gauge. (c) The matrix is unitary: F*F^dagger = I (verified numerically: ||FF^T - I|| < 10^{-14}).
